Khartoum â€” The Ministry of Foreign Affairs has strongly condemned in a statement it issued Tuesday the terrorist aggression launched Sunday, March 25, 2018 by the terrorist Houthi group against a number of cities in Saudi Arabia, using ballistic missiles from inside the Yemeni territories. The aggression has resulted in assassination of a citizen, injuring of a number of innocent people and terrorizing of citizens in a crime that violated all the values, principles and customs. The Foreign Ministry has affirmed the solidarity of Sudan government and people with sister Saudi Arabia and its support to all the measures adopted by Saudi Arabia for safeguarding its security and the safety of its people in the face of such terrorist and criminal acts.